QUALITY CRITERIA

Please use the following section to explain fully how you will provide the following. The sections can be expanded as required. Please ensure you complete all the relevant appendices as well as this Response Section. 

1.





Knowledge & Experience– 20%

Please demonstrate and evidence the knowledge & experience your organisation has including any experience of working with or for Local Authorities, this could be in case study format to include details what you do well and how you overcome any challenges and or barriers and how you addressed them. 





(Your response is limited to 750 words and must be provided in the box below (please expand the box as required), in Ariel font 12pt. Any words in excess of this limit will be discounted. Supporting evidence must be submitted as separate documents and be clearly cross referenced.)



































2.





Project Team– 15%

Please give an organogram of your team including their qualification & experience in this field highlighting the POC & those members who will deliver the training how they will collaborate with the project officer and the team will determine success.







(Your response is limited to 750 words and must be provided in the box below (please expand the box as required), in Ariel font 12pt. Any words in excess of this limit will be discounted. Supporting evidence must be submitted as separate documents and be clearly cross referenced.)







































3.





Proposed programme – 30%

Please provide your proposed programme for our organisation detailing what your processes are to include how you propose, can or will deliver the training, describing the material that will be used which demonstrates and explains how you will achieve the required outputs and outcomes and how they will ensure sustainability of ED&I awareness for our organisation beyond delivery? 



Please be advised that bidders may be requested to deliver this question as a PowerPoint presentation or other agreed format by Zoom or Teams. This will be confirmed via the communication tab and will take place during the week commencing 8 May 2023.





(Your response is limited to 1500 words and must be provided in the box below (please expand the box as required), in Ariel font 12pt. Any words in excess of this limit will be discounted. Supporting evidence must be submitted as separate documents and be clearly referenced.)











































4.





Social Value – 5%

Provide details on Social Value benefits you will deliver under this contract.

Your response should include all community benefits you will provide e.g., apprenticeships, links with local education establishments and support for local businesses affected by the projects.

•	the development of new talent through the modern apprenticeship scheme and work with schools offering work experience to students

•	support to care leavers and children in care

•	improvement to environmental performance through implementation of sustainable development and environmental policies

•	encouraging environmental improvement within the community 

•	support and encouragement to employees to help local community organisations and to participate in activities in our region 

•	employee development 

•	upholding the values of honesty, partnership, and fairness in relationships with stakeholders 

•	contracts which clearly set out agreed terms, conditions, and the basis of the relationship 

•	operating in a way that safeguards against unfair business practices 

•	encouraging suppliers and contractors to adopt responsible business policies and practices for mutual benefit.



(Your response is limited to 500 words and must be provided in the box below (please expand the box as required), in Ariel font 12pt. Any words in excess of this limit will be discounted. Supporting evidence must be submitted as separate documents and be clearly cross referenced.)
